zhamel-zfskey-kmod provides the FreeBSD kernel module used by zhamel to consume
preloaded ZFS wrapping keys during early boot.

The package installs:

  /boot/modules/zhamel_zfskey.ko

The module reads the zhamel preload payload, imports the root pool when needed,
and loads the native OpenZFS wrapping key into the target encryption root.

WWW: https://github.com/hazayan/zhamel-zfskey-kmod
